{"cursor":"12097","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"In mathematics, the 'method of characteristics' is a technique for solving\npartial differential equations. Typically, it applies to first-order equations,\nalthough more generally the method of characteristics is valid for any\nhyperbolic partial differential equation. The method is to reduce a partial\ndifferential equation to a family of ordinary differential equations along which\nthe solution can be integrated from some initial data given on a suitable\nhypersurface.\n","linknr":205,"url":"Method_of_characteristics","recorded":1362583860,"links":18,"instances":[],"pdf":[],"categories":["Partial differential equations"],"headings":["Characteristics of first-order partial differential equation","Example","Characteristics of linear differential operators","Qualitative analysis of characteristics","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/math/c/b/6/cb62d024e48994521eeca55a0ba4599c.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/d/a/b/dabe90b2dca109ea1d97fd5ac244fa79.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/c/e/9/ce9b3247a3772e37537c2a069b9865b1.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/0/8/30868ddc9b1fee7e8218e76d22efd1be.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/b/6/0b6851e8c530c4abfc053cc35b8cbde1.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/2/5/f/25f7482f62621b9539c2aceb05990412.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/f/d/0fda5f5f74696cb16e9287245908b486.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/7/d/87d75ba90adcb3c5d614365919f000b3.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/6/4/1/64189bf4ad837da58be9f3a0c369eeec.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/1/7/8178bac3e07f6d5821500d2f1d1be229.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/7/0/470742f8755bb44b01efa35ef5355793.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/c/a/8/ca8fa237735a75b9779e4db365255789.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/c/e/bcedde638d6d1acdb674d5a719b5ebca.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/3/1/331bc92d2a10f2cc7206b547d5ac1f7f.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/7/1/77137